text:
Saini Sir!! ðŸ™ðŸ™ So, Clubaero it is! The beginning and the end. Jab tak udaane ke kabil rhenge tum sab ko yaad karte rhenge. Thanks for all the contribution. Maze to kafi kiye Techmeets mein, workshops mein, helilabs mein lekin sabse zyada maza bitching mein ata tha. 
What I remember the most, is your sense of humour and apki shayri. Keep spreading joy and laughter in this world. In this chaotic world, nearones like you are a must to survive! There is a certain boldness too in your attitude. Keep it up. We resonated a lot. Will stay in touch and all the best for your career. Baki kafi yaddeyin hai jo milke yaad karte hai.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Automi ke Bhagwan!! Ultimate chapu. Fortunate to meet you. You have been a motivation to the team, to the club and to the council. We met at Robo club and then we stayed in touch forever since then. No words for your contribution. Mech mein bhi kafi chapa hai apne. All the best, stay in touch!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text:
Ruby Ruby! Yaar hum to waise bhi contact mein rhenge hi to practically memoir ka utna point hai nhi. But just for formalities here we go....
E6 was the beginning, ofcourse. Fir zyada memories to tumhare batti consortium ki hai. Lots of bulla sessions. Kafi deep planning of future. Sari cheeze compile karna to mushkil hai so over call someday, but you completed the journey. And thank you, tumhare bina kuch log latak gaye hote. Baki we are always in touch, just a call away. Always stay grounded and prepare tight. See you in a laal batti wali car.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Hey! So I think we first met during Udghosh marketing. Log bol rhe the ki mere wajah se you left, zyada kaam karwata tha ðŸ˜. But anyways, your insights on airbus was helpful for my internship (which never happened, thanks to covid) and then again during the PwC preps. All the best for your journey ahead!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Yo! Moond. Yaar hum to roz roz milte hi rhenge to we'll always stay in touch. Database bhar jayega agar apne memories yahan likhenge toðŸ˜‰
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Gupta bhai! Our chapter began at Drams club I guess. Kafi admirable personality the aap. And baki Antragni ke kisse bhi kafi sunne hai Team se. All the best! Chapte rhena. Hope to stay in touch and cross over someday again!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Aur bhai gajab! Ye dekho khatam hogye sare assignments, exams, quizes, labs. Humare apne chapu coder. We had a perfect combo of a study group. Wahi se shuruat hui thi apni story ki and that got converted to a super-strong between all of us. Every deadline, every exam was full of life and enjoyable because of you. Baki we are always in touch and will stay connected for every other deadline in life.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Alan bhai! You were our motivation at Drams. That energy and dialogue delivery was unforgettable. Uske baad bhi kafi kand sune hai apke. Fulltu machate hue at every moment in life. Power to you. All the best.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Probably the first star from campus to cast in a web series! All the best for your carrer.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: So, you were the first and last in campus jo mere gaal khichta tha. I ain't that chubby and cute anymore. The first image of yours was quite dangerous. Drams mein bhi bahut mara apne mujhe role ke naam pr. But anyways all those memories were worth it. Also those bday surprise plannings, hatsoff to your dedication. Chapu to tum ho hi. Stay in touch and hope to connect soon!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text:
Ram Ram sir ðŸ™! Once upon a time, there were aero guys. Kahani ki shuruat hoti hai aeroclub ke workshop se. Wahan se leker ke har competition, har bitching, har romantic story with dead end, har assignment, har quiz, har lab,  pura dept sath nikala. Epic to get a brother like you. You completed the best study grp ever. And Club ke bhi har din ke alag kaand hai. Jab jab aerospace ke pas rhunga, tum sab ko yaad karunga. We did some real stuff! Atleast guilt mein to nhi jeeyenge. Baki lots of memories, mumbai sagas, acad ran** rone and chill times. Could not have done it without you. Sari cheeze to ab compile nhi ho payegi ab. But we are always in touch so no worries. Kya ghiste the bhai tum, gajab!
Stay high fly high!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Hello Bhai! A sense of surprise when I saw you during orientation. Koi to hai jaan pehcan ka. Met before coming to campus. Tab to alag level hota that apka, super chapu. And fir again crossed on campus. Hope to see you again. Stay in touch!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Archit bhai! Super hospi. Actually you were one amongst the very few jisko dekhke fest mein motivation milta tha logo ko kaam karne ka. Keep that up! And stay connected. All the very best.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: The Taekwondo kid! We met probably at the CPA or Aero club at first. It was nice to connect with you. Safety wali feel ati hai ðŸ˜! All the best.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Hey! So, don't exactly remember when we first met. But the recent most memory of spoiling a surprise is probably the best amongst all others ðŸ˜‚. Definitely, we have to be in touch, you see!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: So! Wing lead the foundation of our relations; aero concreted it. Super cool guy was the impression with some real cool memories. Cheers to your hobbies, your passion and you have that what it takes to succeed. So See you on the other side!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Team AUV nayi gehrai chute hue apke margdarshan pr. Awesome to connect with you. Ultimate chapu to ho hi, so don't need luck wishes. But let's be selfish here; Stay in touch!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Aero It is! The super cheerful person I have met with. Keep spreading that joy. Techkriti events apke bina adhure rhe jate. Thanks for organizing FPV. Really opened new frontiers. Bombay trips were awesome, lets do it once more! And haan didi ki shadi mein nhi aya that mein to uska bhi baki hai.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Barot bhai! The Gujarati aero brother. It was lovely helping you. Ek waisa backup hota hai na ki agar kahi ladai wadai hui to apno ko team up karenge aur pel denge sabko. Tu wo type ka banda tha mere liye. Though aisa mauka kabhi aya nhi ðŸ˜‚. Anyways, hope to see you soon!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: So D6-E6 that's where we met. Thanks for all the SPO stuff and kafi pareshan kiya tumhe uss dauran but worth it tha. That Product and consult cases were also a dose of memory. Above all Pinky ke elections ðŸ¤£. Aur Corona se jaldi bahar aajao, stay safe. Stay in touch, kabhi call karlena jaise uss din msg kiya that waise hi.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Bholu, the top batch wala cse guy. But fortunately, you turned out to be much more humble to us. Waise hum wingees to always touch mein hai hi but still, I guess your main role was to maintain the integrity in the wing. Koi bhi trip ho kahi bhi jana ho, kuch bhi khana ho, kuch bhi khelna ho; always in. The trips, the gpls and the whole time we spent together was worth living. Chalo ab ek aur badi trip ka kuch intezam karo!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Chandra bhai! Waise to apna utna interaction hua nhi physically but ekdo baar kafi important help hui apki madad se. Thanks. And someday we can probably continue the discussion on the inefficacies of admin. Meanwhile, stay strong! and all the best.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Hi! Don't exactly remember when we met first but hope your aero courses were good enough ðŸ˜‰. Baki kafi domains mein chapa hai apne. Keep it up and all the best!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: So Faizan bhai! Robo club was the beginning I guess. Alag level chapter the aap. Have been one of those guys worth the admiration because of the beautiful blend of envious Robotics, awesome passions, great social attitude and above all humbly human. Great to meet you! But you ended up flying the DJI, and I missed the drone shots ðŸ˜¥. You probably don't require best wishes for success, that you'll surely do. So that's it. Stay in touch!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Girish bhai! the coolest Drams guy we have ever seen. Tumhare bina Galaxy mein maza hi nhi ata. Wo roles ke liye compete karna and ek dusre ke katna, nightouts and fir Rishab ko manana, all were beautiful moments. Cool, humble, helpful with a  dose of humour. That's what it takes to be a good human and you have all that. All the very best! Hope to see you soon.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Dechi bhai. Aap jaise kuch logo ki wajah se apna chota sa pyara sa Aero dept intact rheta tha and synergy rheti thi. Sabke almost same assignments and similar submissions. Probably we have been the first dept to genuinely execute a mass bunk! That says all about our bonds. Let's have another dept session together and cherish all those memories. PS> Utna bhi chapu nhi that mein assignments mein.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Bhai aap pehle the jiska dassa dekha tha humne. Apna wing cpi average average tha just because of you alone. In the start, we used to convince (forcefully) ourselves that you are a maggu but as time progressed we were again forced to change that perspective ki dassa wale bhi utne hi cool hote hai jitna baki log. That was an inspiration in itself. Then that Agra trips and tumhare parents ke samne JEE rank awkward situations, and aunty ka dantna, GPLs, Bulla sessions,  and the list goes on and on...Anyways we are always in touch. Starting mein wo startup ke thoughts are still very fresh. Agar kuch bhi karna hai,  just a call awayðŸ˜œ. And yeah seriously, Bangkok trip is on you.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Arey Migrain wale patient. Team Aerial Robotics. See where it is today. It's because we four decided that day not to shut it down. Kafi chidte the yaar tum and fir tumhe manane mein alag hi maza ata tha, after all yahi bate to yaad ayegi. That competition hackathon and oat rooftop night outs, are precious pieces of memories. All the best for your career and kabhi bhulna mat hume!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: IIMA bhai alag level chapa. Aero mein kafi kuch seeka though: memories, bitching and mass bunk. All the best for the future. kabhi bhi kuch bhi kaam ho, ping me. Stay grounded as you have been and all the best for the future ahead.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Aur Hitesh bhai! Aero club it is. Right from day-1 kafi friendly rhe aap. Dher sare nightouts, competitions, foam ghisai, logo ke romatic life pr maze lena, rona bahut sara rona, and full campaign against ones who hampered our culture. All this are unforgettable memories. Waise we'll be in touch to kabhi bhi relish karenge. And all the best for every aspect of your life.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Inshu behen! So, Drams that's where we first met. Small-cute aero family kept us bonded. And then SnT. The techmeet glory was a huge point in my life (not just due to standard reasons but it has something to do with past). And a Big big thanks to you for staying with me during that whole blissful period and keeping everyone motivated. Apke Priyank se liye hue aero notes kaafi kaam aye the. And AUV deserved you. Super impressed with your election move. If you remember, I once said that wanted to have a deep discussion with you on the same, though unfortunately never spared a time for that. Aise hi kafi philosophical discussions hai, that are still in todo. Hope to clear that off! and in a nutshell, you were a real "Changemaker". Stay the same in all spirits and enjoy your life to the fullest. Hope to meet you soon. Meanwhile, stay connected!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: When there's fire; step-0: call the brigade!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Jassi Bhai! Kuch sapne adhure rhe gaye. But anyways thanks a lot to at least mobilise them. A real Punjabi spirit. Man with discipline and an ideal Sports gensec. That's what you are for us. All the best.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Had a lot of fun with you during Aero classes. Indeed a very cheerful guy. Glad to meet you! Hope to see you soon.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Our Wolf of the wall street star! You have always been a motivation for many. Keep it up! and rock that markets. Stay in loop, bahut kaam ane wale ho ðŸ˜‰!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: SnT ðŸ¤ŸðŸ¤Ÿ. Glad ki tum aur Soumya the, warna wo ML wale ps kabhi nhi jeet pate. Great efforts and could have been better if we had been on campus. Anyways, stay in touch!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Sweet sweet Kevlin! Bhai alag level the aap sir. Club ko ek discipline wale bande ki bhi zarurat thi, wo aapne complete kiya. Alwys have been very supportive and growth oriented. Insab cheezo ke sath alag ki charisma tha apka. And jab ye bhola aadmi ghusa ho ya fir bachon ki maar rha ho, wo nazara dekhne layak hota tha. Quite a lot of memories, all there in air! to replenish anytime. All the best. May you get whatever you want in life. And kabhi bhi bhulna mat hume. Baki batteyin phone pe.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Bhai! Quite a journey it had been. Our first meeting is kind of blurry to me but we knew each other quite well. Last mein IME mein collaborate karne ka mauka that but fir zundagi ke kuch aur hi priorities the ðŸ˜‚. Stay in touch. A humble man indeed. And all the very best.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: âœˆâœˆ Aero Family!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Hey! Co-senator and labs group mate. It's been a pleasant journey. All those labs and lab reports. Wo Propulsion wala TA deserves a special mention ðŸ˜‚. Baki you too were quite supportive. Were a better senator than me I guess. All the very best! Power to your leadership desires.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Shi baat hai bhai! Khus rhao maze kro. That's what you have been: a super cool and shant guy. It was a privilege to do the TA project with you. It was quite a fun! ðŸ˜‚ Kafi fraud and masti ke sath khatam kiya usko. It was you jiske wajah se thode chill the hum. Stay like that forever! Hope to see you someday.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: "Tera bhai hai idhar dont worry" thats what you used to say, since the day we sat besides in orientation. It really felt like a big brother is with me. It was amazing to be next to you in sequence and really appreciate your attitude. Stay in touch and all the very best!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: First confession: Loads of respect for whatever you did on/outside campus. We haven't met explicitly much but, you were someone that I kind of envied a little. You were the first, I saw on campus that was a lot into Entrepreneurship. Not just E-Cell but in real. Always wanted to converse with you about these things, but never got a proper moment, maybe someday when we both are a bit more capable of doing so or creating real impact. All the very best! Will keep following you!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Mohammad Shahid Khan! Kya elegant naam laga tha jab pehli baar suna tha. Drams mein definietly kafi maze kiye. And Wing ke liye to anginat cheeze hai jo isme nhi aasakti. Apan to khair touch mein hai hi, live face-to-face baat karte hai then. All the best! Bokaaaaaaaa!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Hey! Campus ane se pehle apan kafi close the. Post campus due to different paths itna connect nhi rha sadly. But nevertheless, Thanks for all those Vibrant assignments and chit chats after classes. Really enjoyed those times and you kept me motivated. Solving all my silly doubts and explaining stuff to me. I hope to stay in touch with you further! All the very best!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Bhai ab kya hi likhu. Hum sab E6-D6 kafi close the waise. That's where we began. I had never anticipated ki tu SnT mein ayega. And frankly before you became Batti coordi, I didn't realise ki itna chapu hai tu. Guitar, Gym, Batti, Microsoft and then GenSec bhi. We got more closer after Techmeet 8 and the elections. And fir 9 mein to macha hi diya. There were many things planned, but online mein we got a bit halted. No worries. Ab Consulting mein chapna. And yeah, do stay connected!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Mathuriya bhai! It was epic meeting you. Be it Inferno, Takneek, Galaxy, or general hall activities, hall day, whatever success we had in the name of hall-12; you had major contribution. We began with drams, then there were tons of memories. especially those motivations during GC events. We indeed continued the legacy! Cheers to you. The HEC election nights were a huge fun part. Overall, Hall need someone bold and brave, and you proved to be a real "Maratha"! Hope to meet you soon.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Hey Naveen! So I had not interacted with you before you become the coordinator. But post that, I respected you a lot. You and Tarish kind of revived and rewoken the Astro club. Congratulations on that!  That itself proves your immense dedication towards things. It was a privilege meeting you! Take care and All the best.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: So, From being a co-senator to GC to CoSHA to President! A true leader indeed! All that done just with the right amount of diligence and a sense of responsibility. Had the campus been offline, much more changes might have been mobilised. But nevertheless, truly admired you right from day-1. Stay ahead and keep connected! Hope to see you someday on the other side.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Arey Sir! so the story goes back to dramatics. Indeed those mehnat wale din were definitely memorable. Kafi feel mein kaam karte the aap sir. And asli maza to galaxy mein aya tha. All those nigh outs, plans, amazing music compilations, ek dusre ke roles katna, chillana, sarcasms, ..................and so on. Post that as an HEC, super supportive. And indeed as an adorable friend. Cheers to all that! You were amongst the few with the potential to bring real change. And abhi kuch past mahino se, ek bhi aisa meme-post nhi hai jo apne share kiya ho and maza an aya hoðŸ˜‚. Bhai kasam se, gajab sense of humour hai apka. Stay smiling and make other too! This world needs people like you. Really looking forward to stay in contact. All th best!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: So, Nitesh Madam! Never interacted with you before became coordinator (as far as I remember). But then, you were the one to keep the balance with that three hyper-active co-corrdis. You are a perfect combo of logical, helpful, calm and straightforward person. Did some great stuff and were a motivation to many. Hope yahi cheeze continue karo. And I am super glad to meet all four of you! Sare competitions, workshops, club events, and other fun stuff was a huge dose of memories that we shared. All the best! and stay in touch.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Arey sir! Kitna rote ho aap. Lekin jitna hi zyada rote ho utna hi zyada chapte ho. Quite an irony. Frankly, I don't clearly remember when we first met. May be it was clubs, may be it was during your IGVC, or may be it was during OnC, wait a lot of things. Ultimate chapu banan koi inse sikhe. Gsoc baki tha wo bhi ho gaya. Actually dreamt of learning some IGVC stuff from you someday but apsos online mein kahan time chala gaya pata nhi chala. This Last course and you doing Dual under a legendary prof. brought us more closer indeed ðŸ˜…. Hope ki Dassa lag jaye tumhara And thanks for everything. Apologies for the rest. But please do stay in touch, bhale fir BT share karne keliye hi sahi!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Hey! Roll number partner. You looked like a very sophisticated and high performance being when we sat next to each other during orientation. You have been ultra nice to everyone. Respect that attitude. And above all, super thank you and congratulations for Game Dev. That's what was missing piece in the council. You took it up at a mammoth pace and standardization. Cheers for that. And will love to stay connected with you forever! #HappyBeings
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar
